UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1952
1 Services Draft Board No. 45; Forum Fellow at the Louisville Courier Journal Class of
2 2003; co-chair of Neighborhood Place Managing Board; board member of Community
3 Partnering for Protecting Children; member of the Steering Committee of Saving Our
4 Children—"A Restorative Justice Initiative"; member of the Advisory Board, State of
5 African American Youth in Metro Louisville; board member of Champions for West
6 Louisville Economic Development; board member of the Neighborhood Place Ujima;
7 and recipient of the District 5 Metro Council Molly Leonard Community Service Award;
8 and
9 WHEREAS, the Senate acknowledges the dedication and exceptional efforts of the
10 Reverend George Clifton Curington, Sr., as a concerned citizen, businessman, devout
11 Christian, and dedicated police officer with the Jefferson County Police Department who
12 worked to improve life in Louisville, Kentucky; and
13 WHEREAS, on January 18th, 2026, the Reverend George Clifton Curington, Sr.,
14 passed from this Earthly life to continue his walk with his Savior in Heaven;
15 NOW, THEREFORE,
16 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
17 Kentucky:
18 Section 1. The Senate expresses its most profound sense of sorrow and extends
19 its sincere condolences to the family, friends, and community of the Reverend George
20 Clifton Curington, Sr., on the sad occasion of his passing.
21 Section 2. The Senate recognizes the manifold positive differences and
22 contributions the Reverend George Clifton Curington, Sr., has made for his fellow
23 residents and the community within Louisville and Jefferson County over the course of
24 his extraordinary life.
25 Section 3. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in loving memory and
26 honor of the Reverend George Clifton Curington, Sr.
27 Section 4. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
